I took myself to the store and had the following incidents:  1) While I was standing by the pick up counter waiting for my beverage, I got sprayed with dirty water from the upside-down fountain used to clean their blender  2) After I finished my beverage, I walked over to their main counter (whether you'd place orders when you are at the store) asking for a refill of a cup of their Pike Place brewed hot coffee. Two store staff looked at me as if I'm out of mind and denied my right to receive a refill. I called their customer service immediately to report this issue, and I got a confirmation that I would have been entitled to a refill of brewed coffee (hot or cold) or tea of any size will I was at the store  Hope the management would step up to educate the employee so that they can provide a better customer service in the future.

Amazing staff, amazing place, best community Starbucks. The staff at the hospital across the street, (including myself as an RN) live and rely on this place! Thank you Community Starbucks! Special shout out to the district manager, today he went above and beyond for me. Today a colleague of mine had an death in the family and was really having a horrific morning..... I ran across the street to get her a tea and croissant. Unfortunately this Starbucks was having plumbing issues and were not fully back online and functioning. Regardless, the district manager came out, profusely apologized, and explained they are almost open. I told him the situation and he got me the tea and croissant regardless of the plumbing issues! Thank you so much! You made my day and made my colleagues day! #PayItForward
